    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (84.61) serving as our cornerstone play, as the combination of a favorable 4.76 xERA matchup against Hancock and a prime #2 spot in the order elevates his floor significantly. **Junior Caminero** (78.33) also demands attention; despite a park factor drag, he benefits from a massive 19% SP skill boost against Gil, making him an elite utility play. **Christian Yelich** (74.32) rounds out our top tier, as his dynamic platoon advantage against Irvin provides the highest efficiency in the outfield today. These three anchors are projected to carry the offensive load, capitalizing on matchups against vulnerable middle-to-back-end rotation arms.\n\nEfficiency scores reveal that our lineup construction is heavily tilted toward platoon advantages, with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (67.85) receiving a notable 14% boost due to his dynamic platoon split against Mlodzinski. While we prioritize elite SB threats, we are proceeding with caution regarding **Hyeseong Kim** (57.09); while his speed remains a weapon against Rocker\u2019s delivery, the #9 spot in the order drags his overall utility below the \"Strong\" threshold. The closest decision on the bench was **Josh Smith** (51.26), who narrowly missed the starting cut. Although **Josh Smith** offers excellent utility against right-handers, the current high-floor performances of **Caleb Durbin** and **Trea Turner**\u2014who both command significant order-based premiums\u2014pushed **Josh Smith** to the bench to preserve our game caps. \n\nManagement must keep a close eye on the weather and potential lineup late-scratches, particularly for **Dillon Dingler** (49.83), whose utility is heavily tied to his #5 spot in the order. We are comfortable benching both **Victor Scott II** (35.39) and **Logan O'Hoppe** (34.19) today; their matchups against Early and Burns are statistically unfavorable enough to warrant protecting their remaining game cap allotments. With **Colt Keith** (69.64) providing reliable production at 1B, the Zebras are well-positioned to maintain category pressure across the board.",
